---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Mac Storage Clear privacy policy. We collect nothing. All data stays on your machine."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 prose prose-neutral">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink/60">
      <strong>Effective Date:</strong> May 6, 2026<br />
      <strong>Last Updated:</strong> May 6, 2026
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10">Introduction</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      This Privacy Policy describes how Ishan Sharma, operating as Mirelle (d/b/a flek.ai)
      ("Mirelle," "we," "us," or "our") handles your information when you use the Mac Storage Clear
      application ("the App") and our website at <a
        href="https://mac-storage-clear.flek.ai"
        class="underline">mac-storage-clear.flek.ai</a
      > (collectively, the "Service").
    </p>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed mt-3">
      The short version: <strong
        >Mac Storage Clear is a fully local desktop application. It does not collect, transmit, or
        store any personal data on our servers. We have no servers.</strong
      >
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10">Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      The App does not collect, transmit, or share any of the following with us or any third party:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 text-ink/80 space-y-1">
      <li>Personal identifiers (name, email, phone number, account ID)</li>
      <li>File contents, file names, or file paths from your disk</li>
      <li>Scan results, deletion history, or quarantine contents</li>
      <li>Device identifiers (UDID, MAC address, advertising identifier)</li>
      <li>IP address, location, or network information</li>
      <li>Usage analytics, crash reports (beyond Apple-provided ones), or telemetry</li>
      <li>Any information from third-party SDKs (we ship none)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10">Data That Stays on Your Mac</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      The App necessarily reads file metadata (sizes, timestamps, names, paths) to perform its
      function. <strong>This information never leaves your Mac.</strong> Specifically:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 text-ink/80 space-y-1">
      <li>
        Scan results are stored in a local SQLite database under <code
          class="text-sm bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
          >~/Library/Application Support/Mac Storage Clear/</code
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        Quarantined files are moved (not copied) to <code
          class="text-sm bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">~/Library/Application Support/Mac Storage
          Clear/quarantine/</code
        >
      </li>
      <li>Theme, layout, and scan preferences are stored in macOS user defaults</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10">Apple-Provided Information</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      If you obtained the App from the Mac App Store, Apple may provide us aggregate, anonymized
      information about installs, ratings, and territory of purchase, governed by Apple's own
      privacy practices. We do not receive any individually identifiable information about you from
      Apple. Apple's standard Mac App Store privacy practices apply: see Apple's <a
        href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/"
        class="underline"
        rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed mt-3">
      If you choose to send a crash report through Apple's crash reporting system, that report goes
      to Apple under Apple's policies. We can view aggregated, anonymized crash data in App Store
      Connect, which we use solely to fix bugs.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10">Children</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      The App is rated 4+ in the Mac App Store. We do not knowingly collect personal information
      from anyone, including children, because we do not collect personal information at all.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10">Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last
      Updated" date at the top of this page. Material changes will be announced via the project
      GitHub repository and the App Store release notes.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10">Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Email:</strong>
      <a href="mailto:support@flek.ai" class="underline">support@flek.ai</a><br />
      <strong>Address:</strong> Ishan Sharma, operating as Mirelle (d/b/a flek.ai), No. 78, 4th
      Cross, 7th Block, Koramangala, Bengaluru Urban, Karnataka, 560095, India<br />
      <strong>Source code:</strong>
      <a href="https://github.com/aanya-send-help/mac-storage-clear" class="underline" rel="noopener"
        >github.com/aanya-send-help/mac-storage-clear</a
      >
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
